cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a model for visual interpretation of deep convolutional neural networks in image classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also utilizes sparse regularization and network perturbation techniques, which are common in machine learning and deep learning research, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with neural networks, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with image classification, which is a common application of multimedia systems, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
